org.smtlib.sexpr

Interface ISexpr

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAccept, IExpr.IAttributeValue, IPos.IPosable, IResponse
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ISexpr.ISeq, ISexpr.IToken<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Lexer.LexBinaryLiteral, Lexer.LexDecimal, Lexer.LexError, Lexer.LexHexLiteral, Lexer.LexKeyword, Lexer.LexNumeral, Lexer.LexStringLiteral, Lexer.LexSymbol, Sexpr, Sexpr.Expr, Sexpr.Seq, Sexpr.Token

    public interface ISexpr
extends IPos.IPosable, IExpr.IAttributeValue, IAccept
    This interface represents S-expressions as used in SMT-LIB; they are used as values for attributes in the standard concrete syntax.
